title: Getting Started
text: Welcome! This page will help you get up and running with the library. Whether you‚Äôre an experienced user or just starting out, follow the steps below to install and begin using the core features.

title: Getting Started
text:
Installation
Follow the instructions below depending on your environment.

Python
pip install your-library-name


R
install.packages("yourLibraryName")


Julia
using Pkg
Pkg.add("YourLibraryName")

You can also clone the GitHub repository if you‚Äôre installing a development version.

title: Getting Started
text:
Basic Usage
Here‚Äôs a minimal example to get started:
import your_library_name as lib

result = lib.run_model(data="path/to/data.csv")
print(result.summary())

title: Getting Started
text:
Requirements
Make sure your system meets the following requirements:

Python 3.8+ or R 4.1+ or Julia 1.8+
Required packages: numpy, pandas, matplotlib, etc.
(Optional) Jupyter Notebook support

title: Research Projects
text:
This section compiles ongoing and completed research projects conducted by DIE-BG that go beyond the scope of our core tools.
Projects hosted here typically involve applied macroeconomic research, forecasting exercises, structural analysis, or experimental modeling initiatives.

title: Research Projects
text:
Purpose
The Projects section serves as a flexible space to:

Document exploratory or complementary studies.
Share empirical investigations not tied to HEFM or HEMI.
Publish internal working drafts, validation reports, or topic-specific models.
Host specialized forecasting tools such as Nowcasting modules.

title: Research Projects
text:
Active Projects

Nowcasting: A real-time indicator system integrating news and statistical signals.

title: Research Projects
text:
How to Navigate
Each project has its own subfolder and includes: - A short description and purpose - Methodological notes and documents - Results, simulations, and visualizations - Supplementary files, when applicable


For more structured modeling tools, visit the HEFM or HEMI sections.

title: About Us
text: We are a technical and research-focused unit dedicated to the development, evaluation, and dissemination of tools and insights for applied economic analysis.

title: About Us
text: We are a technical and research-focused unit dedicated to the development, evaluation, and dissemination of tools and insights for applied economic analysis.

title: About Us
text:
Our Mission
Our mission is to support decision-making and foster technical collaboration by producing robust models, clear documentation, and accessible research outputs.

title: About Us
text:
What We Do
We work on the design and implementation of analytical frameworks, model-based simulations, and empirical projects related to economic dynamics.

title: About Us
text:
Who It‚Äôs For
This website is intended for researchers, analysts, and institutions interested in macroeconomic modeling, forecasting, and applied time series tools.

title: About Us
text:
What You Will Find Here

Theoretical and technical materials

Code libraries and implementation guides

Forecasting results and research outputs

Presentations, downloads, and supporting files

Information about the team and our collaborators

title: About Us
text:
Collaborations
We engage with internal and external partners to share methodologies, co-develop tools, and advance the understanding of key economic phenomena.
